The evidence with the title 'GAO: U.S. corporations pay average effective tax rate of 12.6% - jul ... ' says Jul 1, 2013  ... U.S. companies face the highest official corporate tax rate in the world . But there's a big difference between the rates set out by law and the cash that 's actually collected . Large, profitable U.S. corporations paid an average effective federal tax rate of 12.6 % in 2010, the Government Accountability Office said  ... 
